Adults with physician-diagnosed PsO or PsA (n = 1221), answered
questions about contact with the healthcare system, and treatment
experience and satisfaction. Self-perceived disease severity was
dichotomised to severe (responses of “quite severe”, “very severe”
or “extremely severe”) and non-severe (“not particularly severe”
or “not severe at all”).
