Introduction: DAPSA and MDA are validated composite indices
used in psoriatic arthritis (PsA) to measure disease activity states (1).
Objectives: To assess the proportion of pts treated with secukinumab
(SEC) reaching DAPSA remission (REM) or low disease
activity (LDA) and those who reached either MDA or very low
disease activity (VLDA) at Weeks (wks) 16 and 104 in the FUTURE
2 study (2).
