9.1/-11.4, and -5.9/-7.5/-13.8.
Conclusions: In this 8-y interim analysis, no new safety signals
were observed and safety was consistent with the known safety
profile of ADA. The number of TE deaths in the registry was
below the expected rate. As-observed effectiveness of ADA and
improvement from baseline in PROs were maintained through
96 mos.
