≥10%) was based on the respondent’s estimate of palms of affected
skin (1 palm = 1% BSA).
Results: Among 22,050 individuals questioned, reported prevalence
of PsO and/or PsA was 9.7% (9.4% in Sweden, 9.2% in Denmark,
and 11.9% in Norway); 1264 (5.7%) individuals reported
physician diagnosis and 1221 of these completed the full survey.
